 Location and Access and Tenement Details. 
 The Sabbath gold project is located approximately 12 kilometres northwest of 
 Meekatharra. Access is gained via the Yoothipini Pastoral Station or access via the Mt 
 Seabrook road and then via station tracks to the lease.   
 The Sabbath gold deposit is located in the centre of granted mining lease M51/322 and 
 was granted on the 25th August 1989 and expires on 24th August 2010. The lease is 
 rectangular in shape and comprises a total of 120 hectares with a minimum annual 
 expenditure of $12,000.  
 A review of registered native title sites has been made with no known registered or sites 
 of significance recorded.

 present within the optimum pit shell.

text:
As recommended in the previous reporting period the drill cuttings from the latest 
 program should be collected and submitted to a metallurgical laboratory for bottle rolls to 
 demonstrate and test the expected recovery through a conventional CIP gold circuit. It 
 may also be prudent to complete some first pass heap leach column tests to investigate 
 the potential at heap leaching the mineralized resource, at a lower cut off than what 
 would apply in a toll milling higher grade scenario.

20.text: should also be completed to fine tune expected operating costs.
